title: Robert Sheckley - The Game of X
description:
Say "gesundheit" to the spy who came in from the cold.

All secret agents need to look out for William Nye, now known as Agent X. His recruitment was simple and his legend is brilliant but un-earned. Somehow, he thinks he's the best there is and we all know how pride goeth before a fall.

Here is a spy-tangled novel of undercover misadventure that goes from Paris to Venice by ways of intrigue that 007 never dreamed of--with semi-professional killers, submissive subversives & a swinging Mata Hari from Hunter College. This is upmanship espionage at its funniest.

"Combines ironic wit with suspense to remarkable effect." --John Le Carre


Read by Oliver Wyman
Format: MP3
